FBIS3-2564 "drchi047_w_94012" FBIS-CHI-94-047 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Mar 1994 HONG KONG & MACAO Macao Sino-Portuguese Joint Liaison Group Holds Talks OW2502133694 Beijing XINHUA in English 1325 GMT 25 Feb 94 OW2502133694 Beijing XINHUA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Macao, February 25 (XINHUA) -- The Working Committee of the Sino-Portuguese Joint Liaison Group discussed handling of three major issues during the transitional period in Macao at its 11th meeting held here today. Han Zhaokang, a representative from the Chinese team of the Joint Liaison Group, told reporters after the meeting that the Chinese side mainly listened to the introduction by the Portuguese side on their work to deal with the three major issues, namely localization of public servants and law as well as officialization of Chinese language. The official said that the Chinese side also made initial comment on the Macao Criminal Law handed over by the Portuguese side recently. The official added that the two sides have all stressed the importance and pressingness to handle the three major issues during the transitional period, as 1999 is nearer. Moreover, the two sides also expressed the hope to handle these issues as quickly as possible, he said.
